  <!-- Facilities -->
  <div class="container" id="facilities">
   <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-8">
     <h2>
      Facilities
     </h2>
     <p>
      Oregon State University’s College of Engineering houses the largest near-shore experimental
      facility at an academic institution in the nation — the
      <a href="http://wave.oregonstate.edu/">
       O.H. Hinsdale Wave Research Laboratory
      </a>
      .
      In addition, the research facilities and laboratories available in the School of Civil and
      Construction Engineering are the type found at top engineering schools around the nation, and
      some of them are unique to only a select number of institutions around the country.
     </p>
     Major laboratories include:
     <ul style="font-size:16px">
      <a href="http://cce.oregonstate.edu/geotechnical-field-research-site">
       <li>
        Geotechnical Field Research Site
       </li>
      </a>
      <a href="http://cce.oregonstate.edu/geomatics-laboratory">
       <li>
        Geomatics Laboratories
       </li>
      </a>
      <a href="http://cce.oregonstate.edu/infrastructure-materials-laboratories">
       <li>
        Infrastructure Materials Labs
       </li>
      </a>
      <a href="http://cce.oregonstate.edu/strong-floor">
       <li>
        Structures Lab
       </li>
      </a>
     </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
     <img alt="Facilities" class="image" src="images/tsunami.jpg"/>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div>
  <!-- Research -->
  <div class="container" id="research">
   <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-8">
     <h2>
      Research
     </h2>
     <p>
      Leading researchers in the College of Engineering are collaborating across multiple disciplines to
      address soil liquefaction, which can lead to failure of roads, bridges, buildings, and other critical
      structures, landslide prediction and mitigation, cost-effective improvements to existing
      infrastructure, evacuation routes, and tools to plan for hazards and anticipate risks.
     </p>
     Major research programs include:
     <ul style="font-size:16px">
      <a href="http://cce.oregonstate.edu/coastal-and-ocean-research">
       <li>
        Coastal and Ocean
       </li>
      </a>
      <a href="http://cce.oregonstate.edu/geomatics-research">
       <li>
        Geomatics
       </li>
      </a>
      <a href="http://cce.oregonstate.edu/geotechnical-research">
       <li>
        Geotechnical
       </li>
      </a>
      <a href="http://cce.oregonstate.edu/structural-research">
       <li>
        Structural
       </li>
      </a>
      <a href="http://cce.oregonstate.edu/geotechnical-research">
       <li>
        Transportation
       </li>
      </a>
     </ul>
    </div>
